    <note>Lin Shi [11576] In listing with elder brother. Yun [11575], and as Father-in-law of Zheng Lu [11055], the mingzi character used is the ancient character (using a mountain radical/wrong character, on top) for shi time. See Liu Kezhuang, WJ, 154.8b-9a and CBD entry for shi 'time' and entry for elder brother, Yun. His funerary inscription has a Zhang Bao (not in dataset) as only son-in-law -- either change of name or a second marriage of daughter. Shi was the grandnephew-in-law of Chen Junqing [10884] and I am arbitrarily identifying his grandfather-in-law as Junqing's only identified brother, Zhengqing [10885]. CBD, 2, 1347</note>
